  "body": "EIP-4626 says \"Fees can exists for deposits, yield, AUM, withdrawals, or anything else prescribed by the Vault.\"\r\n\r\nFees for deposits and withdrawals can be hard to implement correctly and compliantly given that there are requirements on how functions interact with fees. For example:\r\n\r\n> previewDeposit MUST be inclusive of deposit fees\r\n\r\nOur current code may not be easily adaptable to add fees with inheritance in a compliant way. This is something we need to review.\r\n\r\nWe didn't include fees by default because there are many things that can have fees added and we didn't want to add the complexity to handle all of them.\r\n\r\nIt may be worth adding support for just deposit and withdrawal fees if those are particularly hard to implement.\r\n\r\nIf we don't add support, we should at least document how users can add the fees to a vault.",
